text: Duné Coetzee (born 14 May 2002) is a South African swimmer. She competed in the women's 400 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. ==References== Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:South African female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for South Africa Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics Category:South African female freestyle swimmers
